The paper discusses the security properties of machine learning models, specifically focusing on unsupervised machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses adversarial attacks, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of clustering algorithms and real-world datasets suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
